"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"featherweight champion\", \"from\": 37, \"to\": 59}, {\"ngram\": \"the 'horrible' treatment\", \"from\": 76, \"to\": 100}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 153}, {\"ngram\": \"her fight\", \"from\": 212, \"to\": 221}, {\"ngram\": \"a 'publicity stunt\", \"from\": 225, \"to\": 243}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Controversy has surrounded the participation of Khelif and Lin at the Olympics in Paris this summer after they were disqualified from the Women's World Championships last year for failing International Boxing Association (IBA) eligibility rules which prevents athletes with XY chromosomes from participating in women's events.\", \"from\": 247, \"to\": 573, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 329, \"end\": 334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999993301572, \"rank\": 6.69812151775725e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 469, \"end\": 472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9626006015803636, \"rank\": 0.03740033591585712, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 521, \"end\": 535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"XY chromosomes\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Controversy\", \"from\": 247, \"to\": 258}, {\"ngram\": \"the participation\", \"from\": 274, \"to\": 291}, {\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 295, \"to\": 301}, {\"ngram\": \"Lin\", \"from\": 306, \"to\": 309}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 313, \"to\": 325}, {\"ngram\": \"the Women's World Championships\", \"from\": 381, \"to\": 412}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 507, \"to\": 515}, {\"ngram\": \"women's events\", \"from\": 558, \"to\": 572}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IBA has not specified why Khelif and Lin failed their gender eligibility tests but has continued to criticise the International Olympic Committee's (IOC) decision to allow both fighters to compete in the women's division in Paris.\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 809, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 579, \"end\": 582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9626006015803636, \"rank\": 0.03740033591585712, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 693, \"end\": 724, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 728, \"end\": 731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.997429572987591e-26, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 803, \"end\": 808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999993301572, \"rank\": 6.69812151775725e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 605, \"to\": 611}, {\"ngram\": \"Lin\", \"from\": 616, \"to\": 619}, {\"ngram\": \"their gender eligibility tests\", \"from\": 627, \"to\": 657}, {\"ngram\": \"both fighters\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 764}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's division\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 799}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both Khelif and Lin competed in the women's division at the Tokyo Olympics three years agoand have always been identified as female since birth.\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 955, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Both Khelif\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 822}, {\"ngram\": \"Lin\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 830}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's division\", \"from\": 843, \"to\": 863}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 867, \"to\": 885}, {\"ngram\": \"three years agoand\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 904}, {\"ngram\": \"birth\", \"from\": 949, \"to\": 954}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Khelif is now guaranteed to win the first Olympic medal of her career after she beat Hungary's Anna Luca Hamori in her 66kg quarter final on Saturday, while Lin will fight Bulgaria's Svetlana Staneva in the 57kg quarter final at 10am on Sunday.\", \"from\": 957, \"to\": 1201, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1042, \"end\": 1049, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.999970466543364, \"rank\": 1.5839390299003635e-05, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}, {\"begin\": 1052, \"end\": 1056, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Freud\", \"score\": 0.9999861998473523, \"rank\": 7.363302792217564e-06, \"text\": \"Anna\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Freud\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Freud\"}, {\"begin\": 1129, \"end\": 1137, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulgaria\", \"score\": 0.999965741762683, \"rank\": 3.384576164735065e-05, \"text\": \"Bulgaria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulgaria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulgaria\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 957, \"to\": 963}, {\"ngram\": \"the first Olympic medal\", \"from\": 989, \"to\": 1012}, {\"ngram\": \"her career\", \"from\": 1016, \"to\": 1026}, {\"ngram\": \"her 66kg quarter\", \"from\": 1072, \"to\": 1088}, {\"ngram\": \"Saturday\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1106}, {\"ngram\": \"Lin\", \"from\": 1114, \"to\": 1117}, {\"ngram\": \"the 57kg quarter\", \"from\": 1160, \"to\": 1176}, {\"ngram\": \"10am\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1190}, {\"ngram\": \"Sunday\", \"from\": 1194, \"to\": 1200}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nicolson, meanwhile, has lost twice to Taiwan's Lin and has also fought and trained with Algeria's Khelif, and points out that both fighters have lost to female opponents on multiple occasions.\", \"from\": 1203, \"to\": 1396, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1203, \"end\": 1211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_MacNeacail\", \"score\": 0.8695019761584565, \"rank\": 0.15008204890422694, \"text\": \"Nicolson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_MacNeacail\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_MacNeacail\"}, {\"begin\": 1242, \"end\": 1248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.7624404433354155, \"rank\": 0.3114989637637586, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 1292, \"end\": 1299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9998423414870381, \"rank\": 0.00015762080729305359, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"both fighters\", \"from\": 1330, \"to\": 1343}, {\"ngram\": \"female opponents\", \"from\": 1357, \"to\": 1373}, {\"ngram\": \"multiple occasions\", \"from\": 1377, \"to\": 1395}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'I have actually fought and sparred both of the girls - they were born female,' Nicolson said in a video on Instagram.\", \"from\": 1398, \"to\": 1516, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1478, \"end\": 1486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_MacNeacail\", \"score\": 0.8695019761584565, \"rank\": 0.15008204890422694, \"text\": \"Nicolson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_MacNeacail\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_MacNeacail\"}, {\"begin\": 1506, \"end\": 1515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2698021324882469e-20, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the girls\", \"from\": 1442, \"to\": 1451}, {\"ngram\": \"a video\", \"from\": 1495, \"to\": 1502}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'They were born with an XY chromosome, which is the male chromosome, but they were born with female bodies - they have the physical attributes of a female.\", \"from\": 1518, \"to\": 1673, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1542, \"end\": 1544, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"score\": 0.9999999359142768, \"rank\": 6.408560034830122e-08, \"text\": \"XY\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the male chromosome\", \"from\": 1566, \"to\": 1585}, {\"ngram\": \"female bodies\", \"from\": 1611, \"to\": 1624}, {\"ngram\": \"the physical attributes\", \"from\": 1637, \"to\": 1660}, {\"ngram\": \"a female\", \"from\": 1664, \"to\": 1672}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'They have grown up as girls, as women.\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1714, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"girls\", \"from\": 1698, \"to\": 1703}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 1708, \"to\": 1713}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They have competed as women the whole time.\", \"from\": 1715, \"to\": 1758, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 1737, \"to\": 1742}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These are not naturally born men who have decided to call themselves women or identify as women to fight women in the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1759, \"to\": 1886, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 1828, \"to\": 1833}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 1849, \"to\": 1854}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 1869}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1873, \"to\": 1885}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'So when the IBA decided to do a chromosome test at the World Championships, it was discovered that these two athletes had XY chromosomes.\", \"from\": 1888, \"to\": 2026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1901, \"end\": 1904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9626006015803636, \"rank\": 0.03740033591585712, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 2011, \"end\": 2025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"XY chromosomes\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a chromosome test\", \"from\": 1919, \"to\": 1936}, {\"ngram\": \"the World Championships\", \"from\": 1940, \"to\": 1963}, {\"ngram\": \"these two athletes\", \"from\": 1988, \"to\": 2006}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'It wasn't a testosterone test, it wasn't like they did not pass something like that.\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2113, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a testosterone test\", \"from\": 2039, \"to\": 2058}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 2093, \"to\": 2102}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It wasn't a physical test, they do not have the physical attributes of a male.\", \"from\": 2114, \"to\": 2192, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a physical test\", \"from\": 2124, \"to\": 2139}, {\"ngram\": \"the physical attributes\", \"from\": 2158, \"to\": 2181}, {\"ngram\": \"a male\", \"from\": 2185, \"to\": 2191}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Differences of Sexual Development are a group of rare conditions involving genes, hormones and reproductive organs.\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2309, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Differences\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2205}, {\"ngram\": \"Sexual Development\", \"from\": 2209, \"to\": 2227}, {\"ngram\": \"a group\", \"from\": 2232, \"to\": 2239}, {\"ngram\": \"rare conditions\", \"from\": 2243, \"to\": 2258}, {\"ngram\": \"genes\", \"from\": 2269, \"to\": 2274}, {\"ngram\": \"hormones\", \"from\": 2276, \"to\": 2284}, {\"ngram\": \"reproductive organs\", \"from\": 2289, \"to\": 2308}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some people with DSDs are raised as female but have XY sex chromosomes and blood testosterone levels in the male range.\", \"from\": 2310, \"to\": 2429, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2362, \"end\": 2364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"score\": 0.9999999359142768, \"rank\": 6.408560034830122e-08, \"text\": \"XY\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Some people\", \"from\": 2310, \"to\": 2321}, {\"ngram\": \"DSDs\", \"from\": 2327, \"to\": 2331}, {\"ngram\": \"blood testosterone levels\", \"from\": 2385, \"to\": 2410}, {\"ngram\": \"the male range\", \"from\": 2414, \"to\": 2428}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'And while it is a bit of a grey area, I think the abuse and the power of the media, and people just jumping on the bandwagon without knowing all the details, is honestly horrible.\", \"from\": 2431, \"to\": 2611, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a bit\", \"from\": 2448, \"to\": 2453}, {\"ngram\": \"a grey area\", \"from\": 2457, \"to\": 2468}, {\"ngram\": \"the abuse\", \"from\": 2478, \"to\": 2487}, {\"ngram\": \"the power\", \"from\": 2492, \"to\": 2501}, {\"ngram\": \"the media\", \"from\": 2505, \"to\": 2514}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 2520, \"to\": 2526}, {\"ngram\": \"the bandwagon\", \"from\": 2543, \"to\": 2556}, {\"ngram\": \"all the details\", \"from\": 2573, \"to\": 2588}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'These girls have represented their country on numerous occasions for many, many years now, as female fighters, and they do not deserve this mistreatment.\", \"from\": 2613, \"to\": 2767, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These girls\", \"from\": 2614, \"to\": 2625}, {\"ngram\": \"their country\", \"from\": 2643, \"to\": 2656}, {\"ngram\": \"numerous occasions\", \"from\": 2660, \"to\": 2678}, {\"ngram\": \"many, many years\", \"from\": 2683, \"to\": 2699}, {\"ngram\": \"female fighters\", \"from\": 2708, \"to\": 2723}, {\"ngram\": \"this mistreatment\", \"from\": 2749, \"to\": 2766}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I think they have been so unfortunate enough to even be in the situation that they are in and to get all this scrutiny as well.\", \"from\": 2768, \"to\": 2895, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the situation\", \"from\": 2827, \"to\": 2840}, {\"ngram\": \"all this scrutiny\", \"from\": 2869, \"to\": 2886}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'These girls have been beat by girls, numerous times, both of them.\", \"from\": 2897, \"to\": 2964, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These girls\", \"from\": 2898, \"to\": 2909}, {\"ngram\": \"girls\", \"from\": 2928, \"to\": 2933}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If they were men and it was dangerous for girls to be fighting them they would be winning gold at everything - they are not.\", \"from\": 2965, \"to\": 3089, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 2978, \"to\": 2981}, {\"ngram\": \"girls\", \"from\": 3007, \"to\": 3012}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 3055, \"to\": 3059}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 3063, \"to\": 3073}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I think that says it all.'\", \"from\": 3090, \"to\": 3116, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nicolson also criticised Carini,who has since offered an apology to Khelif after refusing to shake her handfollowing their fight which lasted just 46 seconds on Thursday.\", \"from\": 3118, \"to\": 3288, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3118, \"end\": 3126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_MacNeacail\", \"score\": 0.8695019761584565, \"rank\": 0.15008204890422694, \"text\": \"Nicolson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_MacNeacail\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_MacNeacail\"}, {\"begin\": 3143, \"end\": 3149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"score\": 0.9999388426452175, \"rank\": 6.116109516524432e-05, \"text\": \"Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an apology\", \"from\": 3172, \"to\": 3182}, {\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 3186, \"to\": 3192}, {\"ngram\": \"their fight\", \"from\": 3235, \"to\": 3246}, {\"ngram\": \"just 46 seconds\", \"from\": 3260, \"to\": 3275}, {\"ngram\": \"Thursday\", \"from\": 3279, \"to\": 3287}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Carini, who was left in tears in the ring, complained to her coach that the fight was 'not fair' before she decided to abandon the contest in the first r